-Every show was excellent. A seamless storyline perfectly curated the playlist, gradually building up emotions. The songs covered every mood and blended beautifully as one.
-The costumes for all 3 of them were flawless, absolutely impeccable.
-The balance between the duo part and the trio part was perfect.
-The solo show by Aing was simply the best. Every swift song was captivating, with every move leaving fans open-mouthed in awe. üòÇ The slow songs showcased her vocal prowess. Her powerful voice didn‚Äôt seem to come just from her diaphragm but from every pore of her being. üòÇ Resonant, resounding, and left me in awe from head to toe.
-The dancing part was the most anticipated part of the concert and was beyond words. I left a part of myself there, unable to move on from the guy in the red pants. It was their first serious dance performance, and it was professional, captivating in every movement, and commanding in every step. Oh my god, so incredibly handsome.
